sentence: Friday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 7,167.21.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 2.94 billion.
Declining stocks led advancers by 2.16 to 1 ratio.
There were 989 advancers and 2134 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 7 stocks reached a 52 week high and 178 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed down -2.34% for the day; a total of -163.99 points.
Western Digital Corporation ( WDC ) had the largest percent change down (-18.18%) while Tesla, Inc. ( TSLA ) had the largest percent change gain rising 5.09%.
The Dow Jones index closed down -1.19% for the day; a total of -296.24 points.
Home Depot, Inc. (The) ( HD ) had the largest percent change down (-3.82%) while Intel Corporation ( INTC ) had the largest percent change gain rising 3.11%.
